<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='292000' id='t-292000'>But in addition, there's something else.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='294000' id='t-294000'>So, if you look at nodes A and B,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='296000' id='t-296000'>they both have six connections.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='298000' id='t-298000'>But if you can see this image [of the network] from a bird's eye view,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='301000' id='t-301000'>you can appreciate that there's something very different</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='303000' id='t-303000'>about nodes A and B.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='305000' id='t-305000'>So, let me ask you this -- I can cultivate this intuition by asking a question --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='308000' id='t-308000'>who would you rather be</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='310000' id='t-310000'>if a deadly germ was spreading through the network, A or B?</span>
